*=============================================================================
* RAM Allocation Map
*=============================================================================

* GPIB address (from DIP switch, 5 bits)
label 0000 gpib_addr

* GPIB transmit buffer: response string built here (M0x01-M0x20)
* Characters are assembled here before being sent over GPIB when talker-addressed

* UART TX buffer: 3-byte command sent to primary controller
label 0022 uart_tx_cmd
label 0023 uart_tx_data_hi
label 0024 uart_tx_data_lo

* GPIB/UART state flags register
* Bit 0: talker mode active
* Bit 1: GPIB addressed-to-talk (ADSMR match)
* Bit 2: device clear pending
* Bit 3: primary controller link active (talk/listen enabled)
* Bit 4: device clear acknowledged
label 0025 link_state_flags

* GPIB serial poll status byte (written to MC68488 SPR)
* Values: 'O'=$4F=OK, 'K'=$4B=UART error, 'M'=$4D=syntax error,
*         'N'=$4E=range error, 'I'=$49=internal error, 'J'=$4A=NMI error
label 0026 spoll_status

* Numeric conversion workspace (M0x27-M0x34)
* Used by decimal_to_binary and binary_to_decimal converters
