* DAC value echo from primary controller
label 0043 dac_value_hi
label 0044 dac_value_lo

* Device status byte (from primary controller via UART framing)
* Bit 7: tracking enabled
* Bit 6: output enabled
* Bit 3: channel A - current limit active
* Bit 2: channel A - voltage limit active
* Bit 1: channel A - constant current mode
* Bit 0: channel A - constant voltage mode
* Bits 3:0 also encode channel B status (shifted)
* Lower nibble indexes into STATUS_STRING_TABLE for mode strings
label 0045 device_status_confirmed
label 0046 device_status_pending

* Error/status code for GPIB responses (2-char, e.g. "OK")
label 0047 error_code_hi
label 0048 error_code_lo

* GPIB EOI received flag (0x7F = EOI seen)
